15 select one of its own members as mayor pro tem. During the absence or physical or mental
16 disability of the mayor for any cause, the mayor pro tem, or in the mayor pro tem's absence
17 or disability for any reason, any one of the council members chosen by a majority vote of
18 the city council, shall be clothed with all the rights and privileges of the mayor and shall
19 perform the duties of the office of the mayor so long as such absence or disability shall
20 continue. Any such absence or disability shall be declared by a majority vote of all
21 council members. The mayor pro tem or selected council member shall sign all contracts
22 and ordinances in which the mayor has a disqualifying financial interest as provided in
23 Section 2.14 of this charter. In the event of a vacancy in the office of mayor pro tem, the
24 city council shall select one of its own members as mayor pro tem at the next regularly held
25 city council meeting following the vacancy."
26 SECTION 2.
27 All laws and parts of laws in conflict with this Act are repealed.
